article.headline: Sacred Heart 81, Wagner 70
article.story: FAIRFIELD, Conn. (AP) -- Maurice Bailey scored 24 of his game-high 26 points in the second half as Sacred Heart beat Wagner 81-70 Wednesday night in a Northeast Conference game. Sacred Heart (5-6, 2-1 NEC) trailed by as many as nine in the second half before pulling away. Bailey also had five steals and six rebounds. Tre Samuels added 13 points and seven rebounds and both Jarrid Frye and Joey Henley scored 13 points for Sacred Heart. Teoine Carroll led Wagner (3-8, 0-1) with 22 points, while Nigel Wyatte (13 points, 12 rebounds) and Sean Munson (11 points, 12 rebounds) each had a double-double. Wagner out-rebounded Sacred Heart 46-31, but the Pioneers shot 56.7 percent in the second half and committed just seven turnovers in the game compared to 22 for the Seahawks. Sacred Heart took the lead with an 11-2 run in the second half that included three 3-pointers. It put the Pioneers ahead 58-53, and they shot 8-of-10 from the free throw line in the final 2:30. Wagner took a 23-14 lead in the first half with a 17-4 run and didn't trail again until Bailey hit a 3-pointer with 8:56 to play in the game.
